Spanish Encomenderos

Conspiracy failed

The uprising failed when they were betrayed to the Spanish authorities by Spanish Encomendero Pedro Sarmiento that pretended cooperation but turned traitor and Antonio Surabao (Susabau), datu of Calamianes.

The rebels were arrested, tried and found guilty of treason.

Executed and their properties wholly or partly confiscated are Agustn de Legazpi, Martn Pangan, Dionisio Fernandez, Omaghicon, Gernimo Bassi, Felipe Salalila, Esteban Taes, and Magt Salamat.

Five leading members were exiled to Mexico: Pedro Balinguit, Pitonggatan, Felipe Salonga, Calao, and Agustn Manuguit. They were the very first natives of the Philippines to settle in New Spain (Mexico).

Exiled from their respective villages and fined were Felipe Amarlangagui, Daulat, Juan Basi, Dionisio Capolon, Luis Balaya, Luis Amanicalao, and five other Tondo chiefs namely Francisco Acta, Gabriel Tuambacar, Calao, Amarlangagui, and Joan Banl. Alonso Lea was acquitted. Still to be sentenced was Amaghicon.
